    {
      "id": "node-class-resolution-demotion-note-contract",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Proposed Contract",
      "position": {
        "x": 1155,
        "y": 330
      },
      "width": 470,
      "height": 360,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Proposed Contract\n\nGraph-native node/class resolution should work like this:\n\n1. A node instance resolves its class from `_classBinding` first.\n2. `_classBinding` only arrives through a bridge action.\n3. No bridge means no class authority; the node remains just a node instance.\n4. `_classBinding` must carry class identity, meaning, defaults, and view entries.\n5. The renderer chooses the right node view from those entries by semantic level.\n6. The editor chooses the right editor view from those same entries.\n7. A bridge provides provenance, not meaning.\n8. Dictionary is support or legacy only; it does not get to discover classes behind the author's back.\n\nThat keeps meaning on the class, provenance on the bridge, and runtime resolution on explicit structure.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
            "graphId": "markdown_class",
            "name": "markdown Node Class",
            "version": "0.1.0",
            "description": "Canonical markdown content node.",
            "createdAt": "2026-02-24T20:05:15Z",
            "updatedAt": "2026-03-24T01:20:00.000Z"
          },
          "intent": "graph",
          "meaning": "Canonical markdown content node.",
          "description": "Canonical markdown content node.",
          "defaults": {},
          "nodeDef": {
            "key": "markdown",
            "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
            "source": "local",
            "version": ">=0.1.0"
          },
          "views": [
            {
              "key": "markdown",
              "intent": "editor",
              "payload": "editor.web",
              "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
              "source": "local",
              "version": ">=0.1.0"
            },
            {
